1
00:00:00,608 --> 00:00:02,142
<i>Previously on "Manhattan"...</i>

2
00:00:02,227 --> 00:00:04,662
Charlie: <i>They said it'd
be just like Cambridge.</i>

3
00:00:04,696 --> 00:00:07,398
-<i> Harvard with sand.</i>
- Charlie, this doesn't look like Cambridge.

4
00:00:07,432 --> 00:00:09,233
Akley: <i>You're looking at the best
equipped lab in the country.</i>

5
00:00:09,235 --> 00:00:12,202
Two Van de Graaff accelerators,
our own cyclotron.

6
00:00:12,237 --> 00:00:13,988
You're building
an atomic bomb.

7
00:00:14,039 --> 00:00:16,040
Is that Frank Winter?

8
00:00:16,074 --> 00:00:18,575
<i>He's got a band of misfits
working on an alternate design.</i>

9
00:00:18,577 --> 00:00:22,079
Whatever we're doing here,
please tell me it's worth it.

10
00:00:22,130 --> 00:00:24,415
I don't know what's gotten into
him since we've gotten here.

11
00:00:24,417 --> 00:00:28,168
Half the time he's brooding and the
other half it's like our honeymoon.

12
00:00:28,219 --> 00:00:29,753
Liza: <i>They're all
like that at first.</i>

13
00:00:29,755 --> 00:00:31,221
<i>It's easier than talking.</i>

14
00:00:31,256 --> 00:00:32,923
<i>Eventually they stop
doing either.</i>

15
00:00:32,974 --> 00:00:34,894
- What?
- No, you can't go to school in New York.

16
00:00:34,926 --> 00:00:37,094
So I'm just supposed to stay
here in this prison camp?

17
00:00:37,096 --> 00:00:39,730
<i>Get knocked up by one of the guards?
Why are we even here?</i>

18
00:00:39,764 --> 00:00:41,265
Everything is a secret.

19
00:00:41,316 --> 00:00:42,599
There's something
I need to tell you.

20
00:00:42,651 --> 00:00:44,685
There's a problem
with Thin Man.

21
00:00:44,736 --> 00:00:47,404
We're dead in the water. So what are we gonna do about it?

22
00:00:47,439 --> 00:00:49,273
What happened between you?

23
00:00:49,324 --> 00:00:51,692
He asked me to do things
no one ever should.

24
00:00:51,743 --> 00:00:54,445
I don't know
who Charlie is anymore.

25
00:00:54,447 --> 00:00:57,414
- I'm going home, Charlie.
- The army won't allow it.

26
00:00:57,449 --> 00:01:00,117
They will if we're divorced.

27
00:01:00,168 --> 00:01:01,585
Are you gonna invite me in?

28
00:01:01,619 --> 00:01:04,088
You can whisper
fission rates in my ear.

29
00:01:04,122 --> 00:01:07,041
<i>Tell me secrets you can't
share with your wife.</i>

30
00:01:07,092 --> 00:01:08,792
There's a leak in this lab.

31
00:01:08,843 --> 00:01:10,627
Someone's been smuggling technical
schematics off the Hill.

32
00:01:10,629 --> 00:01:12,296
My mother died yesterday.

33
00:01:12,347 --> 00:01:14,631
Your new office will be waiting
for you when you get back.

34
00:01:14,633 --> 00:01:17,267
I won't be gone long. They said I
wouldn't have to meet in person.

35
00:01:17,302 --> 00:01:19,803
Only under
extraordinary conditions.

36
00:01:19,805 --> 00:01:22,139
Implosion is taking
center stage.

37
00:01:22,141 --> 00:01:24,641
-<i> They think that you're a spy.</i>
- Charlie.

38
00:01:24,693 --> 00:01:26,310
<i>Your wife is sitting
in the next room.</i>

39
00:01:26,361 --> 00:01:30,147
She has been betraying you for
months with your neighbor.

40
00:01:30,149 --> 00:01:33,283
Frank, it's Charlie. They're
shipping him off the Hill.

41
00:01:33,318 --> 00:01:35,652
- They think he's a traitor.
- What's wrong?

42
00:01:35,654 --> 00:01:37,654
We're building an atomic bomb

43
00:01:37,706 --> 00:01:41,658
that will explode with the
power of 20,000 tons of TNT.

44
00:01:43,461 --> 00:01:45,662
I've done things
I'm not proud of,

45
00:01:45,664 --> 00:01:48,832
but I swear I did all of it
with you and Callie in mind.

46
00:01:48,834 --> 00:01:52,302
A few months ago, a physicist
from another design group and I

47
00:01:52,337 --> 00:01:54,338
<i>engaged in
a secret conspiracy</i>

48
00:01:54,389 --> 00:01:57,674
to co-opt the resources
of his group for implosion.

49
00:01:57,676 --> 00:02:00,844
<i>Akley promoted Charlie Isaacs
to cover up our tracks.</i>

50
00:02:00,846 --> 00:02:03,680
<i>They think he is a spy,
but he had no idea.</i>

51
00:02:03,682 --> 00:02:06,683
You sold the President
of the United States

52
00:02:06,735 --> 00:02:09,019
a Buck Rogers fantasy.

53
00:02:09,021 --> 00:02:10,938
There is a backup plan.

54
00:02:10,989 --> 00:02:12,689
<i>The director of
the implosion group</i>

55
00:02:12,691 --> 00:02:14,608
<i>is one of the brightest
lights on this hill.</i>

56
00:02:14,659 --> 00:02:16,527
<i>This is Dr. Charles Isaacs.</i>

57
00:02:17,578 --> 00:02:20,358
Stimson: <i>What happened
to Frank Winter?</i>

58
00:02:22,367 --> 00:02:25,369
<i>( thunder rumbles )</i>

59
00:02:25,393 --> 00:02:27,893
_

60
00:02:34,546 --> 00:02:37,014
( men shouting )

61
00:02:46,224 --> 00:02:48,392
Hey! Wait!

62
00:02:48,443 --> 00:02:50,561
Charlie!
Just wait! Please.

63
00:02:50,563 --> 00:02:54,565
So the dawn--
the dawn of the atomic age

64
00:02:54,599 --> 00:02:58,268
being ushered in by a Jewish
cardshark whose family crash-landed

65
00:02:58,303 --> 00:03:00,571
- on the American shores less than 50 years ago.
- You shouldn't be down here.

66
00:03:00,573 --> 00:03:02,156
No, just one quote.
One quote.

67
00:03:02,207 --> 00:03:06,493
Would you compare this
to Promethean theft?

68
00:03:06,544 --> 00:03:08,378
Man stealing fire
from the gods?

69
00:03:08,413 --> 00:03:10,380
- Or is it more--
- They pay you by the metaphor?

70
00:03:10,415 --> 00:03:11,665
Hey!

71
00:03:11,716 --> 00:03:13,951
Escort Edward R. Murrow
here to Site B!

72
00:03:13,985 --> 00:03:15,919
If he comes back, you have
permission to shoot him.

73
00:03:15,970 --> 00:03:17,888
What? God.

74
00:03:19,324 --> 00:03:22,593
( Groans )

75
00:03:22,595 --> 00:03:25,195
Whoa! Charlie! Charlie!

76
00:03:25,230 --> 00:03:27,397
Fritz! You're here.

77
00:03:27,432 --> 00:03:30,400
- Yeah.
- I'm glad.

78
00:03:30,435 --> 00:03:33,770
Grab a radio. Make sure the circuit
cables don't short out in the rain.

79
00:03:33,772 --> 00:03:35,772
Whoa, whoa! We're supposed to
meet 10 weather conditions

80
00:03:35,824 --> 00:03:37,107
before we pull the trigger.

81
00:03:37,109 --> 00:03:39,193
Visibility over 45 miles,

82
00:03:39,244 --> 00:03:41,912
- humidity below 85%--
- Yeah, I read the report.

83
00:03:41,946 --> 00:03:45,199
You got to talk to the
colonel, delay the test.

84
00:03:45,250 --> 00:03:47,850
The colonel and I aren't
on the best of terms.

85
00:03:50,455 --> 00:03:52,289
Look, at any given moment,

86
00:03:52,340 --> 00:03:54,958
there are 3,000 thunderstorms
somewhere on the planet.

87
00:03:55,009 --> 00:03:56,627
No, no.
This one is special.

88
00:03:56,629 --> 00:03:59,963
Gulf air at 17,000 feet,
two inversion layers.

89
00:04:00,014 --> 00:04:02,766
They're not going to call
the game for rain.

90
00:04:02,800 --> 00:04:04,801
Let's just hope
it blows over.

91
00:04:04,853 --> 00:04:08,055
It'll blow radioactive fallout
from Roswell to Socorro.

92
00:04:08,106 --> 00:04:09,439
I'm sympathetic.
The Army isn't.

93
00:04:09,474 --> 00:04:11,594
Either way,
I take responsibility.

94
00:04:56,688 --> 00:05:00,324
<i>( Theme music playing )</i>

95
